      <text>4.3.1.6 tan of difference of angles</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="html">
      <text><![CDATA[<p class="HELM_exercise">Exercise</p>
<p>
Using the identities</p>
\[\begin{aligned}
\sin (A-B) &amp;\equiv \sin A\cos B-\cos A\sin B \\
\cos (A -B) &amp;\equiv \cos A\cos B +\sin A\sin B,
\end{aligned}\]
<p>obtain an expansion for \(\tan (A-B)\) in terms of \(\tan A\) and \(\tan B\):
</p>
<p>\(\tan (A-B) =\) [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]]</p>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="html">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>We have</p>
\[\tan(A-B) \equiv \frac{\sin(A - B)}{\cos(A - B)} \equiv \dfrac{\sin A\cos B-\cos A\sin B}{\cos A\cos B+\sin A\sin B}.\]
<p>Dividing every term by \(\cos A\ \cos B\) gives</p>
\[\tan(A-B)\equiv \dfrac{\tan A-\tan B}{1+\tan A\tan B}.\]]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
